notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation Identity Management (IdM) is a centralized authentication, identity management, and authorization solution for both traditional and cloud-based enterprise environments. 

Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):

* Generation of image file fails with Python 3 (JIRA:Rocky Linux-15090)

* SSSD offline causing test-adtrust-install failure (JIRA:Rocky Linux-40894)

* Unconditionally add MS-PAC to global config (JIRA:Rocky Linux-49437)

* Log KDC timeout only once per request [rhel-8.10.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-68634)

* [RFE] add a tool to quickly detect and fix issues with IPA ID ranges [rhel-8.10.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-56920)

This advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
